value.0: Proud officers of the Sith Empire. These men and women spend their days callously orchestrating foul schemes to supplant the Republic as masters of the galaxy, with the promise of power and riches awaiting them in the aftermath of the bloodshed.

Sith warriors are legendary combatants, using the Dark Side of the Force to enhance their physical attributes well beyond what is considered natural. At the same time, it has corrupted them to their very core. As time goes on, they become less human and more and embodiment of the same primal emotions that grant them their strength.

The Sith Assassins, Intelligencia, Inquisitors, or whatever name they adopt on that given day, have a host of responsibilities within the Sith Order. From exploratory missions to uncover more of their lost heritage, to rooting out dissent and spies among the ranks of the Sith, to discovering and exploiting weaknesses in their enemies, the Assassins are highly prized agents of the Empire.

These inexpensive droids litter the surface of worlds conquered by the Sith. Ostensibly there to keep the peace during the transition toward the stability the Sith offer, there's stories abound of these crudely fashioned droids responding to even trivial offenses with lethal force.

The Arkanian Sith Inquisitor stands tall, his once-crisp white skin now faded to a paler, almost sickly hue from years of constant exposure to the dark side. His piercing, pupilless eyes, while sharp, show traces of wearsmall cracks of doubt and exhaustion creeping through the otherwise cold exterior. His hair, once a brilliant white, is now streaked with silver and tinged with the pallor of age, though his face retains the sharp, angular features characteristic of his species. His robes, once pristine and regal, have grown worn and tattered over the years, showing signs of prolonged use and countless battles. A blackened, jagged scar cuts across his right cheek, a souvenir from a past skirmish that has only added to his intimidating presence. He exudes a quiet but unnerving authority. His voice is low and gravelly, carrying the weight of experience. He has grown disillusioned with the endless cycle of training and failure, yet remains an indomitable force in the pursuit of power. Years of molding young acolytes into Sith have left him bitter, yet patient, always watching for the slightest spark of potential that might one day erupt into destructive power. Though he demands absolute loyalty, his patience has thinned over time, and hes grown skeptical of the newer generations, seeing many of them as unworthy of the Sith legacy.

During the Jedi Civil War, average Sith troopers were armed with Sith Assault Guns and Sith sniper rifles for ranged combat and well as standard stun batons and vibroblades for close-quarters combat. All types of Sith troopers were issued vibroblades for close-quarters combat and may have been issued with Sith energy shields as well.
